oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Barn at Blooming Grove
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of a barn at Blooming Grove located in Giles County, Tennessee. There is a group of men, and a few children, gathered in front of the barn along with horses, mules, and plows. On the second story of the barn there is two men and a child. One of the men in the photograph is identified as Henry Randolph.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Barns; Horses; Haylofts; Mules; Plows; Agricultural equipment
